## Teachers are facing new challenges as they have to redesign their courses and adopt innovative teaching practices to meet the expectations of students.

Teachers are faced with many challenges in today’s world, including:

- A growing emphasis on STEM education (science, technology engineering and mathematics) which requires teachers to be familiar with these subjects;
- The need for more personalized learning experiences that help students learn at their own pace;
- The rise of online learning platforms such as Khan Academy or Coursera which offer free courses in various fields;
- The increasing number of students who want to study abroad after high school graduation due to better opportunities available
